items.description: IvySyn is a fully-automated framework for discovering memory error vulnerabilities in Deep Learning (DL) frameworks.

items.name: MINER
items.description: MINER is a REST API fuzzer that utilizes three data-driven designs working together to guide the sequence generation, improve the request generation quality, and capture the unique errors caused by incorrect parameter usage.

items.name: RestTestGen
items.description: RestTestGen is a robust tool and framework designed for automated black-box testing of RESTful web APIs.

items.name: GraphFuzz
items.description: GraphFuzz is an experimental framework for building structure-aware, library API fuzzers.

items.name: Minerva
items.description: Minerva is a browser fuzzer augmented by API mod-ref relations, aiming to synthesize highly-relevant browser API invocations in each test case.

items.name: FANS
items.description: FANS is a fuzzing tool for fuzzing Android native system services. It contains four components: interface collector, interface model extractor, dependency inferer, and fuzzer engine.

items.name: DifuzzRTL
items.description: DifuzzRTL is a differential fuzz testing approach for CPU verification.

items.name: MorFuzz
items.description: MorFuzz is a generic RISC-V processor fuzzing framework that can efficiently detect software triggerable functional bugs.

items.name: SpecFuzz
items.description: SpecFuzz is a tool to enable fuzzing for Spectre vulnerabilities

items.name: Transynther
items.description: Transynther automatically generates and tests building blocks for Meltdown attacks with various faults and microcode assists.

items.name: TEFuzz
items.description: TEFuzz is a tailored fuzzing-based framework to facilitate the detection and exploitation of template escape bugs.

items.name: Witcher
items.description: Witcher is a web application fuzzer that utilizes mutational fuzzing to explore web applications and fault escalation to detect command and SQL injection vulnerabilities.

items.name: CorbFuzz
items.description: CorbFuzz is a state-aware fuzzer for generating as much reponses from a web application as possible without need of setting up database, etc.

items.name: Fluffy
items.description: Fluffy is a multi-transaction differential fuzzer for finding consensus bugs in Ethereum.

items.name: LOKI
items.description: LOKI is a blockchain consensus protocol fuzzing framework that detects the consensus memory related and logic bugs.

items.name: Squirrel
items.description: Squirrel is a fuzzer for database managment systems (DBMSs).
